import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='region', y='wheat_price', data=data)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of wheat prices across different regions?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Wheat Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Region', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat_production', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat production over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Wheat Production'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
